</p>
<p>Ok, <em>now</em> it works.</p>
<h2 id="move-battlemanager-to-the-container">Move BattleManager to the Container <a class="headerlink" href="container-wrapup#move-battlemanager-to-the-container" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Only one more service to go! In <code>battle.php</code>, we create the <code>BattleManager</code>.
Let's move it! Add the <code>private $battleManager</code> property and then the
<code>public function getBattleManager()</code>. Copy the ship loader code to save
time... and so I don't mess up again. Update it for <code>battleManager</code>:
<code>$this-&gt;battleManager = new BattleManager()</code>. And return <code>$this-&gt;battleManager</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="6d0b40b6ed">
